        <div class="flex-none">
          <p class="m0 h5 med-gray">Lesson 0</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-intro underline-link mb4">
        <p><strong>Welcome to HackDesign!</strong> Lesson 0 will prepare you for the lessons you'll start to receive every week, which will guide you towards design literacy and proficiency. Excited?</p>

<p>This week, it's just one link. It happens to be the most powerful design resource I am personally aware of, and I'm excited to share it with you. <em>Objectified</em> has not only changed the way I think about product design, but it also gets me amped up on the potential it has to make a positive impact in people's lives.</p>

<p>Ping me <a href="http://twitter.com/wr" target="_blank">@wr</a> on twitter - let me know what you think.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb4">
        <ol class="m0 p0 list-style-none">
            <li class="mb3">
              <img class="hide left mr2" style="margin-top: 12px;" src="/assets/link_arrow-14256c940ab757198c8500bbd8a885fe4c91932e36ffc5a3d0026861d689c94c.svg" alt="Link arrow" />
              <h3 class="h4 md-h3 serif mt0 mb1 semibold">
                    <a target="_blank" class="red" href="http://www.hustwit.com/category/objectified/">Objectified: A documentary for design</a>
                </h3>
                  <p class="prose m0 underline-link">This film is absolutely crucial to setting the groundwork for you in this course. As you're watching, think about what they're saying and how it would apply to your own work.<br><br><strong>If you’re not able to watch the film elsewhere</strong>, you might be able to watch it on <a href="http://documentaryheaven.com/objectified/" target="_blank">DailyMotion</a>, but it could get taken down at any time. Good luck!</p>
            </li>
        </ol>
      </div>

